Wash and dry all produce (except for green beans). Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve, peel, and mince half the @shallot{1} (mince whole shallot for 4).

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add ginger, garlic, and scallion whites; cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @chicken stock concentrate{1/2}(half) and 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings). Bring to a boil, then stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}. Cover and reduce heat to a gentle simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Pat @pork tenderloin{12%oz} dry with paper towels; season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Fry Seasoning{1%tsp}(1 tsp for 2 servings). Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook, turning occasionally, until browned on all sides and cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board to rest. Wash out pan.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add minced shallot and cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @apricot jam{2%tbsp} and @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}. Simmer until syrupy, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute}. Stir in 1/4 cup water (1/2 cup for 4), half the @brown sugar{1%tbsp} (all for 4), and remaining stock concentrate. Bring to a boil, then lower heat. Let bubble until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Pierce green bean bag with a #fork; place bag on a plate. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: No microwave? No problem! Steam beans in a small pot with a splash of water until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

Carefully transfer @green beans{6%oz} to a medium #bowl. Toss with @sesame oil{1%tbsp}; season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork; season with salt and pepper. Stir any resting juices from pork into pan with glaze. Slice pork crosswise into medallions. Divide rice, pork, and green beans between plates. Drizzle pork with glaze. Top everything with scallion greens and @soy sauce{2%tbsp} to taste.